    {
        "content": "<p>Hi, I'm trying to define the Jacobson ideal of an R-module M as the intersection of the kernels of all homomorphisms from M to simple R-modules. I plan to express it as <code>sInf</code> of the set of these kernels and then prove that this definition is equivalent to the one in Mathlib (<a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Module.jacobson#doc\">docs#Module.jacobson</a>). I'm not sure how to formalize this or if it's the best approach. Could someone help me refine this?</p>",
